      <abstract>
        <p>Court in Milan, Italy, upholds acquittal of former Prime Min Silvio Berlusconi on corruption charges (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A court in Milan upheld the acquittal of the former prime minister, Silvio Berlusconi, on corruption charges. The court upheld a 2004 decision that cleared Mr. Berlusconi, who is Italy's richest man. He had been accused of paying a $434,000 bribe to a Rome judge in 1991 to rule in his favor during the takeover battle for an Italian food conglomerate. The prosecutors had challenged the earlier acquittal and had asked for a five-year sentence.</p>
        <p>ELISABETTA POVOLEDO</p>
      </block>
